President Donald J. Trump has declared an emergency for the Seminole Tribe of Florida and ordered Federal assistance in response to the conditions caused by Hurricane Irma. The Department of Homeland Security's Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) will coordinate all disaster relief efforts. This action aims to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency and provide necessary assistance to save lives, protect property, and ensure public health and safety. FEMA is authorized to identify, mobilize, and provide equipment and resources as needed. Debris removal and emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Justo Hern√°ndez has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.